<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
In Macau, adults appear to be active only in late spring and range in total length 23-28 mm and 6.5-8 mm in maximum width. The species is exclusively nocturnal and readily attracted to artificial lights. The larvae apparently bore into lumber and a variety of trees, such as 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Lauraceae" genus="Machilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Machilus" order="Magnoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Machilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp., 
<taxonomicName class="Aves" family="Sulidae" genus="Morus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Morus alba" order="Ciconiiformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Morus alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and oaks (
<bibRefCitation author="Yiu, V" journalOrPublisher="Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B161" refString="Yiu, V, 2009. Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1. Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" title="Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1." year="2009">Yiu 2009</bibRefCitation>
). The species was introduced into Australia already in the 1960s (
<bibRefCitation author="Duffy, EAJ" journalOrPublisher="British Museum, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B33" refString="Duffy, EAJ, 1963. A monograph of the immature stages of Australasian timber beetles (Cerambycidae). British Museum, London" title="A monograph of the immature stages of Australasian timber beetles (Cerambycidae)." year="1963">Duffy 1963</bibRefCitation>
) and adult specimens emerging from wood furniture and other processed timber have recently been intercepted in several European countries (
<bibRefCitation author="Cocquempot, C" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe royale belge d'Entomologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="201 - 206" refId="B23" refString="Cocquempot, C, Drumont, A, Brosens, D, Ghate, HV, 2014. First interception of the cerambycid beetle Stromatium longicorne (Newman, 1842) in Belgium and distribution notes on other species of Stromatium (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae: Cerambycinae). Bulletin de la Societe royale belge d'Entomologie 150: 201 - 206" title="First interception of the cerambycid beetle Stromatium longicorne (Newman, 1842) in Belgium and distribution notes on other species of Stromatium (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae: Cerambycinae)." volume="150" year="2014">Cocquempot et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
